However, it is mentioned as part of the "Part Tenth: Diyarbekir city and Derik, Savur, Palu and Maden cantons", which implies that Diyarbekir Vilayet was a different administrative entity from Diyarbakır. The documents do not provide information on the capital of Diyarbekir Vilayet, but they suggest that it may have been located in Armenia rather than Turkey.

llama3.1.reason: It actually refers to a vilayet (province) of the Ottoman Empire that existed from 1867 to 1915, which had its capital in Diyarbakır, but in 1915, after the Armenian Genocide, the provincial capital was moved to another location, and Diyarbekir Vilayet ceased to exist.
